TY  - JOUR
AU  - Thesmar, David
AU  - Thoenig, Mathias
T1  - Creative Destruction and Firm Organization Choice*
PY  - 2000
Y1  - 2000/11/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355300555051
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 115
IS  - 4
SP  - 1201
EP  - 1237
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - Firms' organizational choices are influenced by external conditions such as the instability of the product market. In order to address this issue in a macroeconomic perspective, we embed the firm's choice of organizational structure in a model of growth through creative destruction, which induces endogenous market volatility. We find that an increasing supply of skill or globalization may increase the rate of creative destruction, the skill premium, and the skilled wages, and it may depress the unskilled wages. We use an original data set to test the empirical relevance of our theory.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355300555051
ER  - 



